The paper proposes a topic discovery algorithm for unlabeled images based on the bag-of-words framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses sparse principal component analysis (PCA) to extract topics, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions experiments on category prediction, which is a task commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
